The paper focuses on the design and implementation of a system called DSpot that automatically improves existing test cases written by developers. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with improving the quality of software testing. The paper also mentions the use of automated program synthesis techniques (cs.PL) and the evaluation of the system on real-world software projects (cs.SY). Additionally, the system uses machine learning algorithms to generate improved test cases (cs.LG) and involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI).
